This package contains a demonstration of sound morphing using Python and
the Loris library. To run this demo, you must have Python in your path,
and the Loris module in your PYTHONPATH.

	make demo
	
runs the demo, or else simply run the demo script in the Python
interpreter

	python morphdemo.py
	

Loris is an Open Source C++ class library implementing analysis,
manipulation, and synthesis of digitized sounds using the Reassigned
Bandwidth-Enhanced Additive Sound Model, developed by Kelly Fitz and
Lippold Haken at the CERL Sound Group. For more information about Loris
and the Reassigned Bandwidth-Enhanced Additive Sound Model, please visit

	http://www.cerlsoundgroup.org/Loris/
